---

The issue appears to be that although both applications have `--svg` and `--png` options with the "and quit" description, they may not be quitting properly. Let's modify the script to use the `timeout` command to ensure each application terminates after a reasonable time:

---

```diff
      # Process with qlith-mini
      echo "  Rendering with qlith-mini..."
-     "$mini_app" --svg "$mini_output_dir/${name_without_ext}.svg" --png "$mini_output_dir/${name_without_ext}.png" "$html_file"
+     timeout 30 "$mini_app" --svg "$mini_output_dir/${name_without_ext}.svg" --png "$mini_output_dir/${name_without_ext}.png" "$html_file"
+     if [ $? -eq 124 ]; then
+         echo "  WARNING: qlith-mini timed out after 30 seconds"
+     fi
  
      # Process with qlith-pro
      echo "  Rendering with qlith-pro..."
-     "$pro_app" --svg "$pro_output_dir/${name_without_ext}.svg" --png "$pro_output_dir/${name_without_ext}.png" "$html_file"
+     timeout 30 "$pro_app" --svg "$pro_output_dir/${name_without_ext}.svg" --png "$pro_output_dir/${name_without_ext}.png" "$html_file"
+     if [ $? -eq 124 ]; then
+         echo "  WARNING: qlith-pro timed out after 30 seconds"
+     fi
  
      echo "  Done with $filename"
```

```diff
  echo "Starting HTML processing"
  echo "=========================================================="
+ 
+ # Special case for simple test
+ if [ "$test_simple" = true ]; then
+     echo "Creating and rendering a simple test file..."
+     
+     # Create a very simple HTML file
+     test_file="$examples_dir/simple_test.html"
+     cat > "$test_file" << EOL
+ <!DOCTYPE html>
+ <html>
+ <head>
+     <title>Simple Test</title>
+     <style>
+         body {
+             font-family: Arial, sans-serif;
+             margin: 20px;
+         }
+         h1 {
+             color: blue;
+         }
+         p {
+             color: black;
+         }
+     </style>
+ </head>
+ <body>
+     <h1>Hello World</h1>
+     <p>This is a simple test page for Qlith rendering.</p>
+ </body>
+ </html>
+ EOL
+     
+     echo "Created simple test file: $test_file"
+     
+     if [ "$pro_only" = false ]; then
+         echo "  Processing with qlith-mini..."
+         
+         # Run with a longer timeout for the simple file
+         timeout 30 "$mini_app" --svg "$mini_output_dir/simple_test.svg" "$test_file"
+         if [ $? -eq 124 ]; then
+             echo "    WARNING: qlith-mini SVG generation timed out after 30 seconds"
+         elif [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
+             echo "    ERROR: qlith-mini SVG generation failed"
+         else
+             echo "    qlith-mini SVG generation completed successfully"
+         fi
+         
+         timeout 30 "$mini_app" --png "$mini_output_dir/simple_test.png" "$test_file"
+         if [ $? -eq 124 ]; then
+             echo "    WARNING: qlith-mini PNG generation timed out after 30 seconds"
+         elif [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
+             echo "    ERROR: qlith-mini PNG generation failed"
+         else
+             echo "    qlith-mini PNG generation completed successfully"
+         fi
+     fi
+     
+     if [ "$mini_only" = false ]; then
+         echo "  Processing with qlith-pro..."
+         
+         # Run with a longer timeout for the simple file
+         timeout 30 "$pro_app" --svg "$pro_output_dir/simple_test.svg" "$test_file"
+         if [ $? -eq 124 ]; then
+             echo "    WARNING: qlith-pro SVG generation timed out after 30 seconds"
+         elif [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
+             echo "    ERROR: qlith-pro SVG generation failed"
+         else
+             echo "    qlith-pro SVG generation completed successfully"
+         fi
+         
+         timeout 30 "$pro_app" --png "$pro_output_dir/simple_test.png" "$test_file"
+         if [ $? -eq 124 ]; then
+             echo "    WARNING: qlith-pro PNG generation timed out after 30 seconds"
+         elif [ $? -ne 0 ]; then
+             echo "    ERROR: qlith-pro PNG generation failed"
+         else
+             echo "    qlith-pro PNG generation completed successfully"
+         fi
+     fi
+     
+     echo "  Done with simple test"
+     
+     # Exit early if we're only doing the simple test
+     echo "=========================================================="
+     echo "Processing complete!"
+     echo "Output files for qlith-mini are in $mini_output_dir"
+     echo "Output files for qlith-pro are in $pro_output_dir"
+     exit 0
+ fi
  
  # Find all HTML files in examples directory
```
